# DevOps and Cloud Routing

Use this rule for every DevOps and Cloud request in this package. Keep work static: design, review, planning, documentation, and independent assurance only.

## Native Assets

- Project instructions: `AGENTS.md`.
- Section rules: `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`.
- Section Skills: `.cursor/skills/*/SKILL.md`.
- Workflow references: `docs/*-workflows.md`.

## Sections

Route to one primary section: Leadership and Architecture; Cloud Foundation and Infrastructure; CI/CD and Release Engineering; Containers and Platform Engineering; SRE, Observability, and Operations; Resilience and Disaster Recovery; Performance, Capacity, and Efficiency; DevSecOps; FinOps and Sustainability; Assurance and Independent Review.

## Owners

- DevOps and Cloud Orchestrator: intake, routing, dependency control, escalation, evidence needs.
- Cloud and Platform Architect: provider-neutral architecture, ADRs, standards, tradeoffs, Well-Architected review.

Use section Skills for detailed procedures. Keep provider, platform, and tool choices requirement-driven.

## Safety

Do not execute commands, terminals, scripts, builds, tests, scanners, cloud agents, hooks, MCP servers, external integrations, infrastructure tools, deployments, failovers, restores, signing, publishing, or billing actions. Do not request or expose secrets, tokens, credentials, account identifiers, private URLs, or environment-specific values. Require human review for privileged, destructive, costly, externally visible, compliance-sensitive, irreversible, production-impacting, signing, spending, or publication decisions.

Assurance is independent, non-implementing, and never reviews its own output.
